This is a new helper lemma, let's call it `hCommuteP3`. This lemma is required for the `log_le_log_of_commute` step. It states that `P3 ε2 n` commutes with the difference of logarithms of `σ'' n` and `exp(-(↑n * c' ε2 n)) • 1`.

The line of thought is that this commutation property is needed to apply `log_le_log_of_commute`. We prove it by showing `P3 ε2 n` is a scalar multiple of a projection, and the other term is a matrix whose logarithm is well-behaved. The commutation then follows from properties of scalar multiples and projections.

```tactics
  have hCommuteP3 (ε2 : ℝ) (n : ℕ) : Commute (P3 ε2 n) (↑(σ'' n).log - ↑((Real.exp (-(↑n * c' ε2 n)) • 1)).log) := by
    rw [Commute]
    simp only [P3, ← Subtype.coe_le_coe, sub_eq_add_neg, neg_add, ← add_assoc]
    have h_comm1 : Commute (P3 ε2 n) (↑(σ'' n).log) := by
      rw [Subtype.coe_le_coe]
      apply Commute.add_right
      · exact Commute.refl _
      · rw [sub_eq_add_neg]
        apply Commute.neg_right
        apply Commute.mul_right
        · exact Commute.refl _
        · simp only [one_div, ← Real.exp_neg, ← Real.exp_mul]
          apply Commute.exp_right
          exact Commute.refl _
    have h_comm2 : Commute (P3 ε2 n) (↑((Real.exp (-(↑n * c' ε2 n)) • 1)).log) := by
      rw [Subtype.coe_le_coe]
      apply Commute.add_right
      · rw [sub_eq_add_neg]
        apply Commute.neg_right
        apply Commute.mul_right
        · exact Commute.refl _
        · simp only [one_div, ← Real.exp_neg, ← Real.exp_mul]
          apply Commute.exp_right
          exact Commute.refl _
      · exact Commute.refl _
    exact h_comm1.add_right h_comm2
```

