The key insight is that $E_3$ is a projection matrix. The logarithm of a matrix that's diagonal (like a projection matrix) will commute with the projection. This is because the logarithm will also be diagonal in the same basis. The specific structure of the logarithm terms may also contribute to their commutativity.

