The term `((Real.exp (↑n * ((R2 ρ σ).toReal + ε₀ + ε2)) • ↑(σ'' n)).proj_le ↑((fun n_1 => (ℰ n_1 (ρ ⊗ ^S[n_1])).M) n).toMat).log.toReal` is the real logarithm of the matrix `E3`. 

Let's denote `M = (Real.exp (↑n * ((R2 ρ σ).toReal + ε₀ + ε2)) • ↑(σ'' n)).proj_le ↑((fun n_1 => (ℰ n_1 (ρ ⊗ ^S[n_1])).M) n).toMat`.
So we are trying to prove `(1/n) * M.log - S ≤ (R2.toReal + ε₀ + ε2) * M`.
This is equivalent to `M.log - S ≤ n * (R2.toReal + ε₀ + ε2) * M`.

